NgramPredictor
--------------

This is an application to predict the next word that the user going to
say. We can achieve our goal, using ngram model. Basic, the model will
into the too last two words that the user inputed, then calculate the
probability of the next word. It also implement smoothing to account for
missing words that is not in the dictionary. Also the model use backoff
algorithm to jump to lower n-gram if needed

The n-gram predcition algorithm is trained using the subset of the
following data set:

-   News Data set
-   Blogs Data set
-   Twitter Data set

Preprocessing
-------------

Since the 3 given that set is hugh, we just you a random subset of the
data sets to prepresent them.

The following steps was done in order to the new data set:

-   Words were transform to lower
-   Punctuations were removed
-   URLs were removed
-   Remove non-English words
-   Remove english stop words
-   Strip white space
-   Stem the words
-   Strip profanity words

Application
-----------

The user need to input the sentence that the want for predictive model,
the application will read in the given text. After calculation, and
return the 3 most likely word and its log probability via a bar chart
form.
